
'''= We talk about network governments whereby we network all kinds of capability in society to create public value.'''

=Description=

Don Tapscott:

"A platform is an instance of a network. We talk about network governments whereby we network all kinds of capability in society to create public value. One of the ways a network government can do that is by creating a platform where others can self- organize, and you create a platform by just creating raw data.
Governments provide data that enable individual, civil society organizations, private companies and other governments to create their own networks to do something. To solve a problem in society, to deliver a service, rather than governments doing this by themselves as they did  in the past."
(http://www.we-magazine.net/we_leadership-volume-05/who-is-leading-wikirevolutions/)


